0.title: Business Course Equivalency Evaluation Request Form
0.description:
Please use this form if you are an admitted or current WSU student in the Carson College of Business and have a transfer course that does not have a direct equivalency or has an expired date in our Transfer Credit Equivalency Database. If you have a request to update a Transfer Credit Report with an equivalency that currently exists in the database, please email transfer@wsu.edu.
(* Indicates a required field.)

fields.description: Hover/tap for more infoThis form is used by not only students, but also advisors/counselors who are assisting students. If you are student, this is where you fill in your own name. If instead you are an advisor/counselor, then enter the name of the student you are helping.

fields.label: WSU Major
fields.description: This field is optional, but providing us with the student's current or intended major can be helpful in the review of courses for fulfillment of major-specific (i.e. non-UCORE) requirements.

fields.description:
Hover/tap for more infoIf you are a student: if you are working with a counselor/advisor, please provide their name (and email if you have it).
 
If you are a counselor/advisor: this is where you enter your own contact information.

fields.label: HTML Block
fields.content: Note: Please allow two weeks for evaluation request results to be emailed to you and please note that departmental evaluation timeframes may vary. WSU will accept transfer credit for traditional course work you have successfully completed at regionally accredited institutions of higher education. This process does not certify applicability of transfer credit toward degree requirements, which are determined by the academic program you are enrolled at WSU. Students with questions regarding how a transfer equivalency applies toward a WSU degree should consult the WSU catalog or contact transfer@wsu.edu. This information is subject to change.
